<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>HPVCA Website Redesign v3 - Radical Simplification</title>
    <style>
        @page {
            size: 11in 48in;
            margin: 0;
        }
        
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }
        
        body {
            font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            background: #FFFFFF;
            color: #1A2530;
            width: 11in;
            line-height: 1.7;
        }
        
        /* ==================== 
           DESIGN PRINCIPLES APPLIED:
           
           TUFTE:
           - Typography IS the design (no boxes, minimal color)
           - Data integrated into prose
           - Comparative data, not isolated numbers
           - Maximum data-ink ratio
           
           NIELSEN:
           - Question-based navigation (user mental model)
           - Progressive disclosure
           - Single primary action per viewport
           - Clear system status
           ==================== */
        
        /* ==================== 
           HEADER: Question-based navigation
           Users think in questions, not categories
           ==================== */
        
        .header {
            padding: 16px 60px;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #E8E0F0;
            position: relative;
        }
        
        .logo {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 10px;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        
        .logo-mark {
            width: 36px;
            height: 36px;
            background: #7B5BA6;
            border-radius: 8px;
            position: relative;
        }
        
        .logo-mark::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            width: 18px;
            height: 18px;
            border: 2px solid white;
            border-radius: 50%;
            top: 50%;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
        }
        
        .logo-text {
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #1A2530;
        }
        
        .logo-text span {
            color: #7B5BA6;
        }
        
        /* NIELSEN: Question-based nav matches user mental model */
        .main-nav {
            display: flex;
            gap: 32px;
            align-items: center;
        }
        
        .nav-link {
            font-size: 15px;
            color: #2D3E50;
            text-decoration: none;
            padding: 8px 0;
            border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
        }
        
        .nav-link:hover {
            color: #7B5BA6;
            border-bottom-color: #7B5BA6;
        }
        
        .nav-cta {
            background: #7B5BA6;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 14px;
            font-weight: 600;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        
        .nav-donate {
            color: #7B5BA6;
            font-weight: 600;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 14px;
        }
        
        /* Crisis link - always visible, Nielsen: error prevention */
        .crisis-bar {
            background: #5C4080;
            padding: 10px 60px;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 40px;
            font-size: 13px;
        }
        
        .crisis-bar a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        
        .crisis-bar a:first-child {
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #FFEEE5;
        }
        
        /* ==================== 
           HERO: One message, one number, one action
           TUFTE: Integrate data into narrative
           NIELSEN: Single primary action
           ==================== */
        
        .hero {
            padding: 80px 60px;
            max-width: 900px;
        }
        
        .hero h1 {
            font-size: 52px;
            font-weight: 700;
            line-height: 1.15;
            color: #1A2530;
            margin-bottom: 24px;
        }
        
        /* TUFTE: Data integrated into headline, not separate */
        .hero h1 .data {
            color: #7B5BA6;
        }
        
        .hero-lead {
            font-size: 22px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #2D3E50;
            margin-bottom: 32px;
            max-width: 720px;
        }
        
        /* NIELSEN: Single clear action */
        .hero-cta {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
            background: #7B5BA6;
            color: white;
            padding: 16px 32px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 17px;
            font-weight: 600;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        
        .hero-secondary {
            margin-left: 24px;
            color: #5C4080;
            font-size: 17px;
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
        
        /* ==================== 
           TUFTE: Comparative data visualization
           Show relationships, not isolated numbers
           ==================== */
        
        .data-story {
            padding: 60px;
            background: #F9F7FC;
            border-top: 1px solid #E8E0F0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #E8E0F0;
        }
        
        .data-story-inner {
            max-width: 900px;
        }
        
        .data-story h2 {
            font-size: 14px;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
            color: #7B5BA6;
            margin-bottom: 24px;
        }
        
        /* TUFTE: Sparkline-style inline data */
        .data-narrative {
            font-size: 20px;
            line-height: 1.8;
            color: #1A2530;
        }
        
        .data-narrative strong {
            color: #5C4080;
            font-weight: 700;
        }
        
        /* TUFTE: Small multiples - cancer types with relative scale */
        .cancer-breakdown {
            margin-top: 40px;
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(6, 1fr);
            gap: 2px;
        }
        
        .cancer-bar {
            text-align: center;
        }
        
        .cancer-bar-fill {
            background: #7B5BA6;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            border-radius: 2px 2px 0 0;
        }
        
        .cancer-bar:nth-child(1) .cancer-bar-fill { height: 100px; } /* Cervical - most common */
        .cancer-bar:nth-child(2) .cancer-bar-fill { height: 70px; background: #9B7BC6; } /* Head/Neck */
        .cancer-bar:nth-child(3) .cancer-bar-fill { height: 45px; background: #B8A5D3; } /* Anal */
        .cancer-bar:nth-child(4) .cancer-bar-fill { height: 25px; background: #B8A5D3; } /* Vulvar */
        .cancer-bar:nth-child(5) .cancer-bar-fill { height: 20px; background: #D4C8E5; } /* Vaginal */
        .cancer-bar:nth-child(6) .cancer-bar-fill { height: 15px; background: #D4C8E5; } /* Penile */
        
        .cancer-bar-label {
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #2D3E50;
            line-height: 1.3;
        }
        
        .data-footnote {
            margin-top: 16px;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #5A6A7A;
        }
        
        /* ==================== 
           NIELSEN: Progressive disclosure
           Start with questions, reveal answers on demand
           ==================== */
        
        .questions-section {
            padding: 60px;
        }
        
        .questions-section h2 {
            font-size: 32px;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #1A2530;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }
        
        .questions-section > p {
            font-size: 18px;
            color: #5A6A7A;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }
        
        .question-list {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
            gap: 16px;
        }
        
        .question-item {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 16px;
            padding: 20px 24px;
            background: #F9F7FC;
            border-radius: 4px;
            text-decoration: none;
            color: #1A2530;
            border-left: 3px solid transparent;
            transition: all 0.15s;
        }
        
        .question-item:hover {
            background: white;
            border-left-color: #7B5BA6;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
        }
        
        .question-item span {
            font-size: 17px;
            font-weight: 500;
        }
        
        .question-item::after {
            content: '→';
            margin-left: auto;
            color: #7B5BA6;
            font-size: 18px;
        }
        
        /* ==================== 
           TOOL: Clear process, visible status
           NIELSEN: System status visibility
           ==================== */
        
        .tool-section {
            padding: 60px;
            background: #5C4080;
            color: white;
        }
        
        .tool-inner {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 60px;
            align-items: center;
        }
        
        .tool-section h2 {
            font-size: 36px;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }
        
        .tool-section h2 em {
            font-style: normal;
            color: #FFEEE5;
        }
        
        .tool-section p {
            font-size: 18px;
            opacity: 0.9;
            margin-bottom: 24px;
            line-height: 1.7;
        }
        
        .tool-cta {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
            background: white;
            color: #5C4080;
            padding: 14px 28px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 16px;
            font-weight: 600;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        
        /* NIELSEN: Visible process steps */
        .tool-process {
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 32px;
        }
        
        .tool-process-title {
            font-size: 13px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
            opacity: 0.8;
            margin-bottom: 24px;
        }
        
        .process-step {
            display: flex;
            align-items: flex-start;
            gap: 16px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        
        .process-step:last-child {
            margin-bottom: 0;
        }
        
        .step-num {
            width: 28px;
            height: 28px;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
            border-radius: 50%;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-size: 14px;
            font-weight: 700;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }
        
        .step-content strong {
            display: block;
            font-size: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 2px;
        }
        
        .step-content span {
            font-size: 14px;
            opacity: 0.8;
        }
        
        /* ==================== 
           WHO WE ARE: Credibility through specificity
           TUFTE: Specific > general
           ==================== */
        
        .about-section {
            padding: 60px;
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 60px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #E8E0F0;
        }
        
        .about-section h2 {
            font-size: 32px;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #1A2530;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        
        .about-section p {
            font-size: 17px;
            color: #2D3E50;
            line-height: 1.8;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }
        
        /* TUFTE: Specific credentials, not generic claims */
        .founders-row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 32px;
            margin-top: 32px;
        }
        
        .founder {
            flex: 1;
        }
        
        .founder-name {
            font-size: 16px;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #1A2530;
            margin-bottom: 4px;
        }
        
        .founder-title {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #5C4080;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }
        
        .founder-bio {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #5A6A7A;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        
        /* Partners - specific names, not vague claims */
        .partners {
            background: #F9F7FC;
            padding: 32px;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        
        .partners h3 {
            font-size: 13px;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
            color: #5C4080;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }
        
        .partners-list {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #2D3E50;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }
        
        /* ==================== 
           NEWS: Minimal, functional
           TUFTE: Only what's necessary
           ==================== */
        
        .news-section {
            padding: 60px;
        }
        
        .news-header {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: baseline;
            margin-bottom: 32px;
        }
        
        .news-header h2 {
            font-size: 24px;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #1A2530;
        }
        
        .news-header a {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #5C4080;
        }
        
        .news-list {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
            gap: 32px;
        }
        
        .news-item {
            text-decoration: none;
            color: inherit;
        }
        
        .news-item:hover h3 {
            color: #5C4080;
        }
        
        .news-date {
            font-size: 13px;
            color: #7B5BA6;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }
        
        .news-item h3 {
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #1A2530;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            line-height: 1.3;
        }
        
        .news-item p {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #5A6A7A;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }
        
        /* ==================== 
           CTA: One action, clear value
           NIELSEN: Single primary action
           ==================== */
        
        .final-cta {
            padding: 80px 60px;
            background: #F9F7FC;
            text-align: center;
            border-top: 1px solid #E8E0F0;
        }
        
        .final-cta h2 {
            font-size: 32px;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #1A2530;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }
        
        .final-cta p {
            font-size: 18px;
            color: #5A6A7A;
            margin-bottom: 32px;
        }
        
        .final-cta .cta-primary {
            background: #F4A27F;
            color: #1A2530;
            padding: 16px 36px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 17px;
            font-weight: 600;
            text-decoration: none;
            display: inline-block;
        }
        
        .final-cta .cta-secondary {
            margin-left: 24px;
            color: #5C4080;
            font-size: 16px;
        }
        
        /* ==================== 
           FOOTER: Functional, compressed
           TUFTE: Maximum information, minimum ink
           ==================== */
        
        .footer {
            padding: 40px 60px;
            background: white;
            border-top: 1px solid #E8E0F0;
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr;
            gap: 40px;
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #5A6A7A;
        }
        
        .footer-brand p {
            margin-top: 12px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        
        .footer-nav-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
            gap: 24px;
        }
        
        .footer-nav h4 {
            font-size: 12px;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.05em;
            color: #1A2530;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }
        
        .footer-nav ul {
            list-style: none;
        }
        
        .footer-nav li {
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }
        
        .footer-nav a {
            color: #5A6A7A;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        
        .footer-nav a:hover {
            color: #5C4080;
        }
        
        .footer-contact {
            text-align: right;
        }
        
        .footer-contact p {
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }
        
        .social-row {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: flex-end;
            gap: 8px;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }
        
        .social-link {
            width: 28px;
            height: 28px;
            background: #E8E0F0;
            border-radius: 4px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            color: #5C4080;
            font-size: 11px;
            font-weight: 600;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        
        .footer-bottom {
            grid-column: 1 / -1;
            padding-top: 24px;
            border-top: 1px solid #E8E0F0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            font-size: 13px;
        }
        
        .footer-bottom a {
            color: #5A6A7A;
            text-decoration: none;
            margin-left: 24px;
        }
        
        /* ==================== 
           ANNOTATIONS
           ==================== */
        
        .annotation {
            background: #FFFBEB;
            border-left: 4px solid #F4A27F;
            padding: 16px 24px;
            margin: 16px 60px;
            font-size: 13px;
        }
        
        .annotation-title {
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #5C4080;
            font-size: 11px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.05em;
            margin-bottom: 4px;
        }
        
        .annotation p {
            color: #2D3E50;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }
        
        .annotation code {
            background: #F3EFF8;
            padding: 2px 6px;
            border-radius: 3px;
            font-size: 12px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- ANNOTATION: Design Philosophy -->
    <div class="annotation">
        <div class="annotation-title">V3 Design Philosophy</div>
        <p><strong>Tufte:</strong> Typography IS the design. Data woven into prose. Comparative visualization. No decorative elements.<br>
        <strong>Nielsen:</strong> Question-based navigation. Progressive disclosure. One primary action per section. Crisis paths always visible.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Crisis Bar - Always visible -->
    <div class="crisis-bar">
        <a href="#">Just diagnosed? Start here →</a>
        <a href="#">En Español</a>
        <a href="#">For Healthcare Providers</a>
        <a href="#">Search</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="header">
        <a href="/" class="logo">
            <div class="logo-mark"></div>
            <div class="logo-text"><span>HPV</span> Cancers Alliance</div>
        </a>
        <nav class="main-nav">
            <a href="#" class="nav-link">What is HPV?</a>
            <a href="#" class="nav-link">Am I at risk?</a>
            <a href="#" class="nav-link">How do I prevent it?</a>
            <a href="#" class="nav-link">I've been diagnosed</a>
            <a href="#" class="nav-cta">Check My Risk</a>
            <a href="#" class="nav-donate">Donate</a>
        </nav>
    </header>
    
    <!-- ANNOTATION -->
    <div class="annotation">
        <div class="annotation-title">Change: Question-Based Navigation</div>
        <p><strong>Before:</strong> <code>What is HPV? | Prevention | Treatments | Resources | About</code><br>
        <strong>After:</strong> <code>What is HPV? | Am I at risk? | How do I prevent it? | I've been diagnosed</code><br>
        Users think in questions. Navigation should match their mental model, not our org structure.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero: One message -->
    <section class="hero">
        <h1>HPV causes <span class="data">5%</span> of all cancers. Almost all are preventable.</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">If everyone got vaccinated, we'd prevent 1 million cancer diagnoses and 500,000 deaths every year. The vaccine is safe. Screening works. And we're here to help you take the next step.</p>
        <a href="#" class="hero-cta">Find out what to do next →</a>
        <a href="#" class="hero-secondary">Learn about HPV first</a>
    </section>
    
    <!-- ANNOTATION -->
    <div class="annotation">
        <div class="annotation-title">Change: Data Integrated into Narrative</div>
        <p><strong>Before:</strong> Stats in a separate card (5%, 1M+, 6 types) competing with hero text.<br>
        <strong>After:</strong> Data woven into the sentence. "5%" is part of the headline. "1 million" and "500,000" are in the subhead. No separate stats box. Tufte: <em>"Data graphics should draw the viewer into the substance of the data."</em></p>
    </div>

    <!-- Data Story: Comparative visualization -->
    <section class="data-story">
        <div class="data-story-inner">
            <h2>The HPV Story in Numbers</h2>
            <p class="data-narrative">
                <strong>80%</strong> of sexually active adults will get HPV in their lifetime—most will never know it. 
                In <strong>90%</strong> of cases, the infection clears on its own within two years. 
                But for the remaining <strong>10%</strong>, persistent infection can lead to cancer—sometimes decades later. 
                The good news: the HPV vaccine prevents <strong>90%</strong> of these cancers, and it's now approved for adults up to age <strong>45</strong>.
            </p>
            
            <!-- TUFTE: Small multiples showing relative scale -->
            <div class="cancer-breakdown">
                <div class="cancer-bar">
                    <div class="cancer-bar-fill"></div>
                    <div class="cancer-bar-label">Cervical</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cancer-bar">
                    <div class="cancer-bar-fill"></div>
                    <div class="cancer-bar-label">Head &<br>Neck</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cancer-bar">
                    <div class="cancer-bar-fill"></div>
                    <div class="cancer-bar-label">Anal</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cancer-bar">
                    <div class="cancer-bar-fill"></div>
                    <div class="cancer-bar-label">Vulvar</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cancer-bar">
                    <div class="cancer-bar-fill"></div>
                    <div class="cancer-bar-label">Vaginal</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cancer-bar">
                    <div class="cancer-bar-fill"></div>
                    <div class="cancer-bar-label">Penile</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="data-footnote">Relative incidence of HPV-related cancers. Cervical cancer is most common globally; head and neck cancers are rising fastest in the US.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- ANNOTATION -->
    <div class="annotation">
        <div class="annotation-title">Change: Comparative Visualization</div>
        <p><strong>Before:</strong> "6 Types of cancer caused by HPV" — a flat list with no hierarchy.<br>
        <strong>After:</strong> Bar chart showing relative prevalence. User immediately sees cervical is most common, head/neck is rising. Tufte: <em>"Show the data."</em> Not just list it.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Questions: Progressive disclosure -->
    <section class="questions-section">
        <h2>What do you want to know?</h2>
        <p>Click a question to get a clear, evidence-based answer.</p>
        
        <div class="question-list">
            <a href="#" class="question-item">
                <span>Should I get the HPV vaccine?</span>
            </a>
            <a href="#" class="question-item">
                <span>I'm over 26. Is it too late?</span>
            </a>
            <a href="#" class="question-item">
                <span>How do I know if I have HPV?</span>
            </a>
            <a href="#" class="question-item">
                <span>What screening do I need?</span>
            </a>
            <a href="#" class="question-item">
                <span>I tested positive. Now what?</span>
            </a>
            <a href="#" class="question-item">
                <span>Can HPV be cured?</span>
            </a>
            <a href="#" class="question-item">
                <span>How do I talk to my partner about HPV?</span>
            </a>
            <a href="#" class="question-item">
                <span>Is the vaccine safe?</span>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- ANNOTATION -->
    <div class="annotation">
        <div class="annotation-title">Change: Progressive Disclosure via Questions</div>
        <p><strong>Before:</strong> Generic category cards (Education, Screening, Vaccination) with paragraphs of text.<br>
